Rename to positive vs.negative feelings

change_names <- function(naming){
naming %>%
  str_replace("A", "no") %>%
  str_replace("B", "no") %>%
  str_replace("C", "neutral") %>%
  str_replace("D", "yes") %>%
  str_replace("E", "yes")
}

change_names2 <- function(naming){
naming %>%
  str_replace("A", "very good") %>%
  str_replace("B", "okay") %>%
  str_replace("C", "bad")
}

change_names3 <- function(naming){
naming %>%
  str_replace("A", "yes") %>%
  str_replace("B", "no") %>%
  str_replace("C", "not sure")
}

Sample statistic

sampling <- all %>%
  group_by(pre_or_post) %>%
  count(all) %>%
  mutate(prop = (n / sum(n))) %>%
  ungroup(pre_or_post) %>%
  group_by(all) %>%
  mutate(diff(prop)) %>%
  filter(pre_or_post == "pre") %>%
  filter(all == "yes") %>%
  select(-pre_or_post, -all, -n, -prop) %>%
  pull()
## Adding missing grouping variables: `all`
sampling
## [1] 0.04377249

Permute

set.seed(2019)
permute_all <- all %>%
  specify(response = all, explanatory = pre_or_post, success = "yes") %>%
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>%
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "permute") %>%
  calculate(stat = "diff in props", order = c("post", "pre"))

Permute visualization

ggplot(data = permute_all, 
       mapping = aes(x = stat)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  labs(title = "Distribution of difference in proportion", subtitle = "of girls who want to take more STEM courses before and after Ignite", x = "Difference in Proportion of Girls", y = "Frequency") 
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

permute_all %>%
  filter(stat >= sampling) %>%
  summarise((p_value = n()/1000) * 2)

Yes vs.No (no neutral)

neutral <- function(no){
  no %>%
  str_replace("neutral", "no")
}

empower_bind$all <- neutral(empower_bind$all)
  
empower_bind <- empower_bind %>%
  filter(!is.na(all))

Bootstrap

set.seed(2019)
boot_community <- empower_bind %>%
  specify(response = all, explanatory = pre_or_post, success = "yes") %>%
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "bootstrap") %>%
  calculate(stat = "diff in props", order = c("post", "pre"))
ggplot(data = boot_community, mapping = aes(x = stat)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.01) +
  labs(title = "Difference in Proportion of Girls", subtitle = "Who Want to Do More for Their Community after Ignite",
       x = "Difference in Proportion", 
       y = "Frequency")

boot_community %>%
  summarize(lower_bound = quantile(stat, 0.005),

Sample statistic

info <- empower_bind %>%
  group_by(pre_or_post) %>%
  count(all) %>%
  mutate(prop = (n / sum(n))) %>%
  ungroup(pre_or_post) %>%
  group_by(all) %>%
  mutate(diff(prop)) %>%
  filter(pre_or_post == "pre") %>%
  filter(all == "yes") %>%
  select(-pre_or_post, -all, -n, -prop) %>%
  pull()

Permute

set.seed(2019)
permute <- empower_bind %>%
  specify(response = all, explanatory = pre_or_post, success = "yes") %>%
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>%
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "permute") %>%
  calculate(stat = "diff in props", order = c("post", "pre"))
